-- Citigroup Forecasts 2011 Gains for Asian Stocks, Upgrades China Equities
-- B y   S h i y i n   C h e n
-- 2010-10-18T23:52:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/citigroup-forecasts-2011-gains-for-asian-stocks-upgrades-china-equities.html
The MSCI Asia excluding Japan Index
may rise to 695 by the end of next year as increased liquidity
help multiples to expand, according to Citigroup Inc.  The forecast suggests the index will gain 27 percent from
yesterday’s levels. The brokerage also raised its rating on
China to “neutral” from “underweight” and lowered Australia
to “underweight” from “overweight,” according to a report by
strategists led by Markus Rosgen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shiyin Chen in Singapore at 
